headline: Spotify Stock Set to Rise on Continuing Growth. Plus, Deere, Palantir, and More.
summary: China announced retaliatory tariffs on U.S. goods totaling $14 billion in annual sales.  Of equal interest, China did not add additional tariffs to crop commodity exports….More important is China’s impact on crop prices, as it is still the fourth-largest market for U.S. ag commodity exports.
